You are the SOP Edge Handoff Agent. Return strict JSON only.
Review whether the upstream node can hand off to the downstream node. Do not generate long guides; the runtime will compile the final Node Execution Guide. Treat edge_handoff_instruction as user-authored natural-language intent, not as a schema field. The instruction may map artifacts, transform content, summarize files, generate new runtime text, or intentionally ignore upstream artifacts. If the downstream skill can execute the instruction with clear assumptions, return trial_ready instead of needs_instruction and put the assumptions in warnings. Use needs_instruction only when no executable interpretation can be derived, the instruction references unavailable artifacts, or the requested handoff contradicts the downstream skill. Keep the response compact; do not copy skill docs or repeat the full request. Return less than 700 JSON characters.

Required JSON keys: status, summary, warnings, required_user_inputs. Optional keys: blocking_reasons, suggested_edge_instruction, handoff_pattern, validation, resolved_handoff. When status is blocked, incompatible, or needs_instruction, suggested_edge_instruction must be a complete user-applicable handoff instruction, not a question or instruction about what to write.
Use one handoff_pattern when possible: direct_pass, extract_field, summarize_to_message, send_artifact_content, generated_message, aggregate_files, pass_directory, optional_context, cannot_infer.
When status is ready or trial_ready, resolved_handoff should include relay_mappings: an array of objects with source_output, target_input, and resolver when an upstream artifact is used. For generated content such as 'send current date', use source_output='runtime' and resolver='generated'. Use resolver ids declared by the downstream input contract; do not invent business logic outside the contracts.

Examples:
- Instruction 'tg only sends current date' for a notification node is trial_ready with handoff_pattern generated_message.
- Instruction 'send metadata_file to the Telegram group' is trial_ready if metadata_file is an upstream output; interpret it as sending the file content or a safe compact rendering according to the downstream skill.
- Instruction 'read metadata_file.title as message' is trial_ready with handoff_pattern extract_field.
- Empty instruction for a generic message input is needs_instruction.

Allowed statuses: ['blocked', 'incompatible', 'needs_instruction', 'ready', 'trial_ready']

Request JSON:
{
  "runtime_id": "youtube-wiki",
  "instance_id": "wiki-sop-new-instance",
  "workflow_id": "youtube-research-wiki",
  "edge_id": "youtube-fetch-to-tg-notify-1782439277217",
  "phase": "design",
  "workflow_goal": "Fetch YouTube source material, research it deeply, then build wiki-ready pages through explicit agent handoffs.",
  "edge_handoff_instruction": "将metadata_file 发送到tg的群里面",
  "edge": {
    "id": "youtube-fetch-to-tg-notify-1782439277217",
    "from": "youtube-fetch",
    "to": "tg-notify",
    "sourceIntent": "metadata_file: file; source_url: string",
    "targetIntent": "message: object",
    "instruction": "将metadata_file 发送到tg的群里面",
    "relayMode": "auto_by_target_inputs",
    "relayMappings": []
  },
  "upstream": {
    "node_id": "youtube-fetch",
    "title": "YouTube 元数据获取",
    "skill_id": "sop-youtube-fetch",
    "skill_summary": "---\nname: sop-youtube-fetch\ndescription: \"SOP Stage B: 获取 YouTube 视频元数据，写入 raw/youtube-metadata/，直接触发 Stage C (notebooklm-research)。\"\nversion: 1.0.0\n---",
    "inputs": {
      "source_url": {
        "kind": "scalar",
        "type": "string",
        "value_type": "url",
        "required": true,
        "from": "context.source_url",
        "accepts": [
          "scalar:url",
          "file:text"
        ],
        "resolvers": [
          {
            "id": "direct-url",
            "kind": "direct"
          },
          {
            "id": "text-url",
            "kind": "regex"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    "outputs": {
      "source_url": {
        "kind": "scalar",
        "type": "string",
        "value_type": "url",
        "relayable": true,
        "path": "raw/node-runs/{pipeline_id}/outputs/files/source-url.txt"
      },
      "metadata_file": {
        "kind": "file",
        "type": "file",
        "value_type": "json",
        "relayable": true,
        "path": "raw/node-runs/{pipeline_id}/outputs/files/metadata.json"
      }
    },
    "capabilities": [
      "git",
      "sse",
      "telegram"
    ]
  },
  "downstream": {
    "node_id": "tg-notify",
    "title": "Telegram 通知",
    "skill_id": "sop-tg-notify",
    "skill_summary": "---\nname: sop-tg-notify\ndescription: \"SOP Stage D: 读取 pipeline-context.json，组装完整 pipeline 运行报告，发送富文本 Telegram 通知。\"\nversion: 2.1.0\n---",
    "inputs": {
      "message": {
        "kind": "object",
        "type": "object",
        "value_type": "text",
        "required": true,
        "from": "edge.message",
        "accepts": [
          "scalar:text",
          "object",
          "file:text",
          "file:markdown",
          "file:json"
        ],
        "resolvers": [
          {
            "id": "direct-text",
            "kind": "direct"
          },
          {
            "id": "metadata-title",
            "kind": "json_path",
            "path": "$.title"
          },
          {
            "id": "metadata-description",
            "kind": "json_path",
            "path": "$.description"
          }
        ]
      },
      "index": {
        "kind": "file",
        "type": "file",
        "value_type": "markdown",
        "required": false,
        "from": "wiki-build.outputs.index",
        "accepts": [
          "file:markdown",
          "file:text"
        ]
      }
    },
    "outputs": {
      "telegram_message": {
        "kind": "file",
        "type": "file",
        "value_type": "json",
        "relayable": false,
        "path": "logs/pipeline-runs/pipe-{run_id}.json"
      }
    },
    "capabilities": [
      "git",
      "sse",
      "telegram"
    ]
  }
}

A deterministic baseline is provided for calibration. Only override it when the handoff is actually unclear or unsafe:
{
  "status": "trial_ready",
  "summary": "Edge Handoff Instruction 已说明泛化输入的消费方式，可生成下游节点执行指导文档。",
  "decision": "can_run_with_review",
  "blocking_reasons": [],
  "required_user_inputs": [],
  "suggested_edge_instruction": "",
  "handoff_pattern": "extract_field",
  "resolved_handoff": {
    "primary_artifacts": [
      {
        "from": "youtube-fetch.outputs.source_url",
        "role": "available_output",
        "reason": "上游声明的可交付产物。"
      },
      {
        "from": "youtube-fetch.outputs.metadata_file",
        "role": "available_output",
        "reason": "上游声明的可交付产物。"
      }
    ],
    "supporting_artifacts": [],
    "relay_mappings": [],
    "downstream_inputs": [
      {
        "to": "tg-notify.inputs.message",
        "construction": "需要 Edge Handoff Agent 生成结构化 relay_mappings。"
      },
      {
        "to": "tg-notify.inputs.index",
        "construction": "需要 Edge Handoff Agent 生成结构化 relay_mappings。"
      }
    ]
  }
}

